                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Kulangsu/144a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Amoy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVitty</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-20T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 20, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Tension at and over Kulangsu appears, on basis of all reports available to us
                    now, to be satisfactorily relaxing; and Department hopes that it will not again
                    become acute. Department desires that, in case Municipal Council or any foreign
                    or local elements manifest tendencies toward unduly challenging or arousing
                    susceptibilities of the Japanese, you discreetly exert influence toward
                    encouraging exercise of self-restraint.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping and Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
